{"questionId":"2721340","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi></math>. Give your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mrow><mi>c</mi></mfrac></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi></math> (from part (a))&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>attempts to solve for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>(for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><